name: Jalen Hurts
summary: Philadelphia Eagles quarterback Jalen Hurts sustained a concussion during the game against the Washington Commanders, leading to his exit. As a result, he was replaced by Kenny Pickett. Despite having a significant lead, the Eagles ultimately suffered a stunning last-second defeat, marking the end of their 10-game winning streak. The injury to Hurts, along with Pickett's own injury, contributed to the Eagles' downfall. Further updates on Hurts' condition and his potential return date are still pending.

name: Buccaneers vs Cowboys
summary: The Dallas Cowboys pulled off a major upset on Sunday Night Football, defeating the Tampa Bay Buccaneers 26-24. The win dealt a significant blow to the Buccaneers' playoff hopes, while keeping the Cowboys' slim postseason chances alive. The Cowboys defense was the story of the game, forcing three turnovers including two interceptions and a fumble. Dak Prescott led the Cowboys' offense with 226 passing yards and a touchdown, while Tony Pollard rushed for 75 yards and a touchdown. The Buccaneers were held to just 24 points, their lowest total of the season. Tom Brady threw for 253 yards and a touchdown, but was also intercepted twice. The loss drops the Buccaneers to 7-7, while the Cowboys improve to 6-9.
